@node "Intro" "Introduction"
                               Introduction

 DFDKeep will go through your BBS mail capture files, and save selected
 files to an output file. You can choose to Skip or Keep each message with
 a click of the mouse. Or use the Search function to search for any message
 containing the search keyword you entered. Saving found messages can be
 done in automatic or interactive modes. It also has a Twit filter so you
 don't have to see messages you don't want to.

 You can Quit in the middle of an input mail file then reload it later.
 DFDKeep will remember where you left off and start with the last message
 displayed in the previous session.

 DFDKeep was written for a friend, WaltZ. A few years back I ran across
 a program called "Keep v1.1" by Tim Grantham. I "hacked" it slightly to
 work with Skyline BBS mail captures (I ran Atredes/Skyline BBS back then)
 and gave it to two friends - and they still used it seven years later.
 There is another handy program called "KeyFiler v1.0" by John Motsinger
 that searches through mail by keyword. I decided to combine the two ideas
 and asked what else I should add. I was well into writing DFDKeep when
 WaltZ tells me he came up with "Keep v1.5" by Tim G. (which I havn't seen
 yet). Had I known Tim recently updated his program I would never have
 written DFDKeep, I don't like to feel that I'm "ripping" other peoples
 ideas... but I didn't know... so wrote it. And from what WaltZ tells me,
 the new features he asked me for are now in the new "Keep v1.5". Which
 just proves that great minds think alike. But all credit for the great
 idea of a "Keep" type program goes to Tim. And all the credit for the
 great idea of a "KeyFiler" type program goes to John. Thanks guys!


 DFDKeep is written in ARexx, then crunched using The ReXXmAsHeR v0.4g.
@endnode

@node "Install" "Install / Setup"
Install / Setup

 You can install DFDKeep by hand or by clicking the Install button below.

 Install button only works if the Current Directory is where you unarched
 the DFDKeep archive. Or you can cd to the dir you unarched to and from
 the shell enter "RX Install_DFDKeep.rexx".

 By Hand:

 1. Copy the library file included in this archive libs/ directory to your
    LIBS: assigned directory.

    libs/apig.library        (v3.3 included in archive)

    1a. You must also have the following libraries in your LIBS: assigned
        directory;
 
        asl.library              (supplied with WB2+)
        mathieeedoubbas.library  (supplied with WB2+)
        rexxsyslib.library       (supplied with WB2+)
        rexxsupport.library      (supplied with WB2+)

 2. Copy the included files "DFDKeep", "Run_DFDKeep", and "Run_DFDKeep.info"
    to .... well... wherever you want. If you do not plan on starting
    DFDKeep from the Workbench, then you don't need the two Run_files at
    all - just copy DFDKeep to your C: directory. But from Workbench you
    will need the two Run_files - this is because if you run a RexxMasher
    compressed file from an icon, it will give a "Software Error" on exit.
    It is a (very nasty) little bug in the RexxMasher program.

 You must have RexxMast already running before you start DFDKeep. You can
 either drop RexxMast in your WBStartup drawer, or add it to your
 user-startup.

 DFDKeep requires Amiga OS 2.0+.
 It has been tested and found to work on my Amiga 2500 with OS 2.05 and 3.1,
 and WaltZ Amiga 3000 with OS 2.04.

                          @{" Install DFDKeep Now " rx "Install_DFDKeep.rexx"}  

@endnode

